y%20back-of-the-envelope%20math%2C%20these%20kinds%20of%20lower-tier%20salaries%20hover%20around%20US%20national%20median%20earnings.%20A%20like-for-like%20comparison%20is%20difficult%2C%20given%20Google's%20total%20compensation%20figures%20can%20include%20bonus%20and%20equity%2C%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fwkyeng.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20median%20US%20wage%20is%20%241%2C100%20a%20week%2C%20equating%20roughly%20to%20%2457%2C200%20a%20year.%20In%202021%2C%20real%20median%20household%20income%20was%20%2470%2C784%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fpublications%2F2022%2Fdemo%2Fp60-276.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20census%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20many%20Googlers%20earn%20far%20above%20this.%20The%20median%20total%20compensation%20for%20a%20Google%20employee%20in%202022%20was%20%24279%2C802%2C%20according%20to%20the%20leaked%20data.%C2%A0The%20highest-paid%20software%20engineers%20can%20make%20up%20to%20%24718%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20base%20salary.%20They%20can%20also%20receive%20bonuses%20of%20up%20to%20%24605%2C000.%20This%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-needed-to-be-top-earner-us-states-ranking-2023-1%5C%22%3Eput%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20top%201%25%20of%20earners%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20whether%20the%20same%20workers%20received%20the%20maximum%20salary%20and%20the%20maximum%20bonus%2C%20but%20if%20they%20did%20they'd%20be%20taking%20home%20a%20staggering%20%241.3%20million%20dollars%20a%20year.%20That%20doesn't%20factor%20in%20equity%20either%2C%20which%20can%20range%20up%20to%20an%20additional%20%241.5%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContinuing%20our%20rudimentary%20math%2C%20which%20doesn't%20account%20for%20taxes%2C%20someone%20earning%2