20tapered%20legs'%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bild%20Lilli%20doll%20made%20of%20all%20rigid%20plastic%20with%20jointed%20limbs%2C%20blond%20hair%20in%20a%20ponytail%20with%20a%20front%20curl%2C%20painted%20black%20earrings%20and%20heels.%20The%20doll%20is%20dressed%20in%20a%20blue%20and%20white%20polka%20dot%20dress.%20Photographed%20on%20a%20plain%20black%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b1606ff9a25900194755ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221860%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESSPL%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Handler's%20imagination%20was%20sparked%20on%20a%20family%20trip%20around%20Europe%20in%20summer%201956.%20Walking%20past%20a%20toy%20shop%20in%20the%20Swiss%20Alps%2C%20both%20Handler%20and%20her%20daughter%20were%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20transfixed%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20sight%20of%20a%20doll%20they%20saw%20in%20the%20window%20%E2%80%93%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-history-bild-lilli-mattel-ruth-handler-german-comic-strip-2023-5%5C%22%3EBild%20Lilli%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBarbara%20and%20I%20lingered%20outside%20that%20shop%20for%20the%20longest%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBild%20Lilli%20had%20first%20appeared%20in%20comic%20strips%20in%20German%20tabloid%20paper%20Bild%20Zeitung.%20Lilli%2C%20a%20cartoon%20secretary%2C%20%26quot%3Bpursued%20rich%20men%20by%20striking%20provocative%20poses%20in%20revealing%20clothes%20and%20spouting%20comic-strip%20bubbles%20of%20suggestive%20dialogue%2C%26quot%3B%20Robin%20Gerber%20wrote%20in%20%26quot%3BBarbie%20and%20Ruth%2C%26quot%3B%20her%202000%20biography%20of%20Handler.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20began%20making%20Lilli%20dolls%20in%201955%20featuring%20a%20heart-shaped%20face%2C%20glued-on%20high%20blonde%20ponytail%2C%20sharp%20red%20pout%2C%20and%20eyes%20that%20glanced%20sideways%2C%20complete%20with%20blue%20shadow%20and%20winged%20liner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20'Lilli'%20doll%20was%20the%20embodiment%20of%20an%20idea%20I'd%20pitched%20to%20Elliot%20and%20our%20other%20Mattel%20toy%20designers%20some%20five%20years%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%20While%20Lilli's%20face%20was%20%26quot%3Btoo%20hard-looking%20and%20cartoonish%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20body%20%26quot%3Bwas%20another%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHere%20were%20the%20breasts%2C%20the%20small%20waist%2C%20the%20long%2C%20tapered%20legs%20I%20had%20enthusiastically%20described%20for%20the%20designers%20all%20those%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBarbie%20was%20made%20less%20'curvaceous'%20but%20still%20looked%20a%20lot%20like%20Lilli%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Composite%20pictures%20of%20Barbie%20doll%20(left)%2C%20Bild%20Lilli%20doll%20(right)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646f73f9d6d9d2001856e5e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFrederic%20Neema%2FSygma%20via%20Getty%20Images%2C%20Chesnot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Handler%20returned%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20later%20that%20summer%2C%20she%20showed%20Lilli%20to%20Mattel's%20team%20and%20finally%20managed%20to%20convince%20her%20colleagues%20of%20her%20idea.%20The%20toy%20company%20ultimately%20made%20a%20manufacturing%20agreement%20in%20Japan%2C%20where%20production%20was%20cheaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandler%20tweaked%20Lilli's%20look.%20Her%20curved%20eyebrows%20were%20swapped%20for%20dramatic%20arches%20and%20her%20lips%20were%20softened.%20Handler%20also%20gave%20Barbie%20tiny%20individual%20toes%2C%20unlike%20Lilli%2C%20whose%20legs%20simply%20transitioned%20into%20her%20shoes.%20Lilli's%20hard%20plastic%20was%20switched%20for%20a%20softer%20material%2C%20her%20hair%20was%20rooted%2C%20and%20she%20was%20made%20less%20%26quot%3Bcurvaceous%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Barbie%20still%20had%20Lilli's%20high%20blonde%20ponytail%2C%20delicate%20nose%2C%20and%20winged%20eyes.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-history-bild-lilli-mattel-ruth-handler-german-comic-strip-2023-5%5C%22%3ELilli%20and%20her%20new%20sister%20were%20barely%20distinguishable%20except%20to%20the%20new%20doll's%20creator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Gerber%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandler%20wanted%20Barbie%20to%20be%20a%20blank%20canvas%20for%20the%20children%20who%20played%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20began%20sculpting%20Barbie's%20face%2C%20I%20insisted%20that%20it%20not%20be%20too%20pretty%20or%20contain%20too%20much%20personality%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20worried%20that%20if%20she%20were%20too%20glamorous%2C%20little%20girls%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20identify%20with%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandler%20didn't%20just%20want%20a%20doll%2C%20however.%20She%20wanted%20a%20whole%20suite%20of%20exquisitely-detailed%20clothes%20and%20accessories%2C%20too%2C%20with%20tiny%20zippers%2C%20buttons%2C%20and%20hems.%20She%20hoped%20that%20ultimately%20these%20would%20contribute%20more%20revenues%20than%20the%20dolls%20themselves%20%E2%80%93%20unlike%20Lilli%2C%20whose%20clothes%20weren't%20sold%20separately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandler%20consulted%20the%20psychologist%20Ernest%20Dichter%20during%20Barbie's%20development%2C%20too.%20After%20interviewing%20191%20girls%20and%2045%20mothers%2C%20he%20suggested%20enlarging%20the%20doll's%20breasts%20but%20also%20downplaying%20her%20%26quot%3Bsexual%20overtones%26quot%3B%20to%20appeal%20to%20mothers%2C%20according%20to%20Gerber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLittle%20girls%20dream%20of%20being%20curvaceous%2C%20dreamy%2C%20exciting%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20once%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fwgbh%2Ftheymadeamerica%2Ffilmmore%2Fs3_pt.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20%E2%80%93%20some%20day%20%E2%80%93%20to%20have%20gorgeous%20clothes%2C%20be%20chic%2C%20and%20look%20like%20movie%20stars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandler%20had%20wanted%20to%20name%20the%20doll%20after%20her%20daughter's%20nickname%2C%20Babs.%20But%20that%20had%20already%20been%20taken%20%E2%80%93%20as%20had%20Barbara.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-ken-named-after-sister-brother-mattel-ruth-handler-siblings-2023-5%5C%22%3ESo%20Handler%20settled%20for%20Barbie%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20gave%20the%20doll%20the%20full%20name%20Barbara%20Millicent%20Roberts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReadying%20Barbie%20for%20mass%20production%20was%20a%20slow%20process.%20%26quot%3BOver%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20the%20time%20it%20took%20to%20bring%20the%20doll%20to%20market%2C%20slowly%20but%20surely%20the%20concept%20gained%20momentum%20and%20enthusiasm%20at%20Mattel%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20be%20very%20persuasive%20in%20getting%20others%20to%20see%20the%20light.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBuyers%20didn't%20care%20about%20Barbie%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223543%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20first%20Barbie%2C%20who%20came%20out%20in%201959.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b160af9751e300192a1cd6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222663%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20first%20Barbie%2C%20who%20came%20out%20in%201959.%3Cp%3EFrederic%20Neema%2FSygma%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBarbie%20was%20finally%20unveiled%20to%20the%20public%20at%20the%20National%20Toy%20Fair%20in%20New%20York%20on%20March%209%2C%201959%2C%20which%20is%20now%20known%20as%20her%20birthday.%20The%2011-inch%20doll%20took%20over%20a%20room%20at%20the%20New%20Yorker%20Hotel%2C%20the%20centerpiece%20of%20which%20was%20a%20Barbie%20in%20a%20wedding%20dress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20leaving%20for%20New%20York%2C%20Mattel%20told%20its%20manufacturers%20to%20increase%20supply%2C%20setting%20a%20%26quot%3Bmodest%26quot%3B%20forecast%20for%20the%20first%20year%20of%20one%20million%20dolls%20and%20two%20million%20pieces%20of%20clothing%2C%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vintagebabs.com%2Fx_1959-barbie.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20version%20of%20Barbie%20to%20hit%20the%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20cost%20%243%20and%20wore%20a%20black-and-white%20striped%20swimsuit%2C%20small%20black%20heels%2C%20sunglasses%2C%20and%20hooped%20earrings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditional%20items%20of%20clothing%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesmachine.nytimes.com%2Ftimesmachine%2F1959%2F02%2F07%2Fissue.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%2022-piece%20wardrobe%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20sold%20at%20between%20%241%20and%20%243.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20razor%20and%20the%20razor%20blade%20theory%3A%20Sell%20the%20razor%20at%20a%20reasonable%20price%20and%20people%20will%20buy%20the%20razor%20blades%20%E2%80%93%20or%20clothes%2C%20in%20our%20case%20%E2%80%93%20to%20go%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMattel%20was%20already%20an%20industry%20heavyweight%20with%20a%20booming%20portfolio%20by%20the%20time%20of%20the%201959%20toy%20fair.%20But%20there%20wasn't%20much%20interest%20in%20Barbie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20quarter%20of%20Mattel's%20usual%20buyers%20ordered%20%26quot%3Bgood-sized%20quantities%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20doll%20at%20the%20toy%20fair%2C%20and%20the%20same%20proportion%20ordered%20a%20%26quot%3Btoken%20number%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%20The%20remaining%20half%20%26quot%3Bwanted%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20saying%20little%20girls%20only%20wanted%20to%20play%20with%20baby%20dolls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20their%20biggest%20objection%20was%20that%20Barbie%20had%20breasts.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20%26quot%3Bher%20'figure'%20typified%20what%20the%20feminine%20ideal%20was%20in%20the%20late%201950s%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHandler%20wired%20Mattel's%20Japanese%20manufacturers%20to%20cut%20production%20by%2040%25%2C%20before%20going%20to%20her%20hotel%20room%20to%20cry%2C%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESales%20started%20to%20climb%20and%20parents%20didn't%20object%20as%20much%20as%20buyers%20expected%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20old%20Barbie%20dolls%20and%20one%20Ken%20doll%20shown%20at%20an%20auction%20in%202000%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b162109751e300192a1d65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFiona%20Hanson%2FPA%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20interest%20in%20the%20doll%20started%20growing%20as%20schools%20broke%20up%20for%20summer.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D9hhjjhYGQtY%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20first%20Barbie%20TV%20commercial%3C%2Fa%3E%20aired%20during%20the%20Mickey%20Mouse%20Club%20that%20year.%20Suddenly%2C%20Mattel%20could%20hardly%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20demand%20for%20Barbie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20in%20the%20retail%20business%20use%20an%20expression%20for%20a%20popular%20product%20%E2%80%93%20they%20say%20it%20'walks'%20off%20the%20counter%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBarbie%20didn't%20walk.%20She%20ran.%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnewsround%2F47441963%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAround%20350%2C000%20dolls%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20sold%20in%20the%20first%20year.%20Bild%20Lilli%20sold%20130%2C000%20dolls%20in%20her%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMattel%20ramped%20up%20production%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it%20took%20us%20three%20years%20to%20even%20come%20close%20to%20catching%20up%20with%20the%20demand%20a%20little%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarbie%20became%20a%20must-have%20toy%20for%20young%20girls%20in%20the%20US%20and%20beyond.%20According%20to%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcontent.time.com%2Ftime%2Fsubscriber%2Farticle%2F0%2C33009%2C874558%2C00.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1962%20article%20by%20Time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Barbie%20%26quot%3Bappeals%20to%20little%20girls%20because%20it%20looks%20'grown%20up'%20and%20to%20their%20parents%20because%20it%20is%20inexpensive.%26quot%3B%20Handler%20said%20she%20got%20letters%20from%20mothers%20%26quot%3Bgrateful%20to%20us%20for%20getting%20their%20daughters%20to%20be%20more%20conscious%20about%20style%20and%20good%20grooming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20production%20scaled%20up%2C%20Handler%20and%20other%20Mattel%20designers%20kept%20a%20%26quot%3Bscrupulous%20eye%20on%20the%20incoming%20shiploads%20of%20finished%20dolls%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1963%2F04%2F21%2Farchives%2Fcase-of-the-teenage-doll-barble-is-old-enough-to-have-dates-now-and.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D84%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0wrote%20in%201963.%20%26quot%3BRejects%20go%20back%20to%20Japan%20to%20be%20sold%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%201968%2C%20Barbie%20had%20brought%20in%20more%20than%20%24500%20million%20in%20retail%20sales%2C%20including%20the%20sales%20of%20103%20million%20costume%20sets%2C%20with%20around%2010%2C000%20workers%20in%20Japan%20producing%20the%20doll%20and%20her%20myriad%20accessories%2C%20Gerber%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDesigning%20Ken%20led%20to%20an%20argument%20over%20how%20prominent%20to%20make%20his%20crotch%