in%20the%20franchise%20were%20named%20for%20Handler's%20relatives.%20These%20included%20Allan%2C%20%26quot%3BKen's%20best%20friend%2C%26quot%3B%20who%20was%20named%20for%20Handler's%20son-in-law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fshop.mattel.com%2Fpages%2Fbarbie-diversity-evolution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristie%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20released%20in%201968%20as%20a%20friend%20of%20Barbie%20after%20a%20failed%20launch%20of%20a%20Black%20version%20of%20Francie%20the%20year%20before.%20Christie%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20Black%20fashion%20dolls%20on%20the%20market.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20overwhelmingly%20accepted%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%20The%20first%20Black%20and%20Hispanic%20Barbies%20weren't%20released%20until%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fshop.mattel.com%2Fpages%2Fbarbie-diversity-evolution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1980%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%3A%20Prior%20to%20that%2C%20Mattel's%20non-white%20dolls%20were%20always%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bfriends%20of%20Barbie.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMattel%20was%20quick%20to%20expand%20the%20Barbie%20line%20beyond%20just%20dolls%2C%20too.%20In%201962%2C%20only%20three%20years%20after%20the%20doll%20first%20hit%20shelves%2C%20her%20most%20iconic%20accessory%2C%20the%20Barbie%20Dreamhouse%2C%20was%20released.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBarbie%20became%20'prettier%20and%20prettier'%20as%20the%20years%20went%20by%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224974%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Barbie%20dolls%20are%20displayed%20during%20an%20exceptional%20exhibition%20dedicated%20to%20the%20Barbie%20doll%20at%20%26quot%3BLa%20Nef%20des%20jouets%26quot%3B%20on%20March%208%2C%202019%20in%20Soultz-Haut-Rhin%2C%20France.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b1640ef9a25900194756e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpposable%20limbs%20and%20different%20hairstyles%20were%20among%20the%20innovations%20in%20Barbie's%20early%20years.%3Cp%3EChesnot%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMattel%20was%20keen%20to%20innovate%20and%20regularly%20released%20new%20dolls%20to%20reflect%20manufacturing%20advancements%2C%20including%20more%20posable%20ones%20with%20bendable%20limbs.%20The%20first%20talking%20doll%20came%20out%20in%201968%2C%20uttering%20phrases%20like%20%26quot%3BHelp%20me%20fix%20my%20hair%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20I'll%20call%20Ken.%26quot%3B%20A%20%26quot%3BGrowing%20Up%26quot%3B%20version%20of%20Skipper%20came%20out%20in%201975%2C%20whose%20arm%20could%20be%20rotated%20to%20make%20her%20grow%20taller%2C%20get%20small%20breasts%2C%20and%20have%20a%20slimmer%20waistline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarbie's%20style%20also%20changed%20over%20the%20years%20in%20response%20to%20fashion%20trends%2C%20demand%20from%20customers%2C%20and%20Mattel's%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Handler%20had%20wanted%20Barbie%20to%20be%20a%20blank%20canvas%20for%20young%20girls%2C%20Mattel's%20advertising%20agency%20%26quot%3Bwanted%20to%20play%20up%20the%20glamorous%20aspects%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BEventually%2C%20I%20began%20to%20lose%20the%20battle%20because%20consumers%20seemed%20to%20prefer%20the%20glamorous%20side%20of%20Barbie.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20designers%20made%20the%20doll%20prettier%20and%20prettier%20as%20the%20years%20went%20by%20because%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20little%20girls%20were%20not%20intimidated%20by%20Barbie's%20looks%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeciding%20which%20outfits%20to%20manufacture%20was%20difficult%20because%20of%20the%20lag%20between%20Barbie's%20clothes%20being%20designed%20and%20hitting%20stores.%20%26quot%3BWe%20never%20tried%20to%20set%20fashion%2C%20we%20just%20tried%20to%20anticipate%20what%20the%20fashions%20were%20going%20to%20be%20by%20the%20time%20the%20product%20came%20on%20the%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKen%20changed%20over%20time%2C%20too.%20His%20physique%20was%20altered%20in%201963%20to%20give%20him%20%26quot%3Bbroad%20shoulders%2C%20a%20tapered%20waist%20and%20somewhat%20more%20muscle%26quot%3B%20than%20previous%20models%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20his%20makers%20kept%20him%20on%20the%20scrawny%20side%20to%20make%20him%20easier%20to%20dress%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1963%2F04%2F21%2Farchives%2Fcase-of-the-teenage-doll-barble-is-old-enough-to-have-dates-now-and.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D84%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20publication%20described%20him%20as%20having%20%26quot%3Ban%20earnest%2C%20unsophisticated%20look.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%201960s%2C%20both%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20were%20restyled.%20Barbie%20had%20%26quot%3Bplastic%20surgery%2C%26quot%3B%20giving%20her%20a%20%26quot%3Bwider-eyed%2C%20less-sultry%2C%20more%20teenager-like%20face%20and%20longer%20hair%2C%26quot%3B%20while%C2%A0Ken%20got%20%26quot%3Ba%20hunkier%20build%2C%20a%20handsomer%20face%2C%20longer%20hair%2C%20and%20a%20healthier%20skin%20tone%2C%26quot%3B%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20early%201970s%2C%20Ken%20%26quot%3Breflected%20society's%20attitude%20that%20it%20was%20now%20acceptable%20for%20men%20to%20primp%20and%20be%20vain%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20the%20release%20of%20a%20%26quot%3BMod%20Hair%20Ken%26quot%3B%20with%20shoulder-length%2C%20rooted%20hair%2C%20Handler%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20decades%2C%20Barbie%20has%20received%20fierce%20criticism%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbarbie-ken-dolls-would-look-like-real-life-unrealistic-body-2019-6%5C%22%3Ecreating%20unrealistic%20body%20standards%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%201970%20Women's%20Strike%20for%20Equality%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20some%20marchers%20chanted%20%26quot%3BI%