y%202023%20Likely%20to%20Be%20Warmest%20Month%20on%20Record%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21104628%2FUntitled-design-7.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJuly%20of%202023%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20month%20on%20record%20in%20%E2%80%9Chundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%2C%20of%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20NASA%E2%80%99s%20top%20scientists%20in%20a%20roundtable%20with%20reporters%2C%20warning%20that%20the%20heat%20is%20only%20going%20to%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20seeing%20unprecedented%20changes%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20The%20heatwaves%20that%20we%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fsiestas-and-chilling-at-church-how-to-beat-the-heat-in-germany%2Fa-66279154%5C%22%3Eseeing%20in%20the%20US%2C%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20China%2C%20and%20demolishing%20records%20left%2C%20right%20and%20centre.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20surprise%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gavin%20Schmidt%2C%20Director%20of%20the%20NASA%20Goddard%20Institute%20for%20Space%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJune%20of%202023%20was%20already%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcerberus-heat-wave-record-breaking-temperatures-hit-mediterranean%2Fa-66221924%5C%22%3Ehottest%20June%20on%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20July%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20the%20hottest%20month%20overall.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20from%20science%20is%20that%20human%20activity%2C%20principally%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%2C%20are%20unequivocally%20causing%20the%20warming%20we%20are%20seeing%20on%20our%20planet%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0Kate%20Calvin%2C%20NASA%20chief%20scientist%20and%20senior%20climate%20adviser%2C%20said%20at%20the%20same%20briefing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJust%20the%20beginning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%E2%80%99s%20scientists%20clarified%20that%20data%20collected%20and%20analysed%20by%20the%20institute%20had%20already%20pointed%20towards%20this.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20a%20decade-on-decade%20increase%20in%20temperatures%20throughout%20the%20last%20four%20decades%2C%E2%80%9D%20Schmidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20space%20agency%20last%20saw%20such%20a%20spike%20in%20temperatures%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-2020-ties-2016-as-hottest-year-on-record%2Fa-56166308%5C%22%3EJuly%20and%20August%20of%202016%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20super%20El%20Nino%20event%C2%A0in%20the%20winter%20of%202015-2016.%20While%20there%20is%20another%20such%20event%20currently%20in%20the%20works%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20haven%E2%80%99t%20gotten%20there%20with%20the%20current%20El%20Nino%20event%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0Schmidt%20said.%20He%C2%A0added%20that%20it%20has%20%E2%80%9Conly%20just%20emerged.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20heatwaves%20seen%20at%20present%20are%20due%20to%20an%20overall%20warmth%20across%20the%20world%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20oceans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20been%20seeing%20record-breaking%20sea%20surface%20temperatures%2C%20even%20outside%20of%20the%20tropics%2C%20for%20many%20months%20now.%20And%20we%20will%20anticipate%20that%20is%20going%20to%20continue%2C%20and%20the%20reason%20why%20we%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20going%20to%20continue%2C%20is%20because%20we%20continue%20to%20put%20greenhouse%20gasses%20into%20the%20atmosphere%2C%E2%80%9D%20Schmidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20scientist%20assigned%20a%20%E2%80%9C50-50%20chance%E2%80%9D%20that%202023%20will%20be%20the%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%2C%20only%20to%20be%20beaten%20by%202024%20which%20will%20be%20even%20warmer%20because%20of%20the%20ascendant%20El%20Nino.%20Other%20scientists%20assigned%20an%2080%25%20chance%20of%C2%A02023%20being%20the%20warmest%20in%20the%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fnasa-warns-july-2023-likely-to-be-warmest-month-on-record%2Fa-66304390%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20publishe