%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20380px)%2085vw%2C%20380px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21121203%2Fmistress-bhatia-hi-res.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22380%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21121203%2Fmistress-bhatia-hi-res.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21121203%2Fmistress-bhatia-hi-res-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21121203%2Fmistress-bhatia-hi-res-683x1024.jpg%20683w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664329%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22570%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESujata%20Massey.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Mistress%20of%20Bhatia%20House%3APerveen%20Mistry%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EInvestigates.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Penguin%20Random%20House%20(2023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESujata%20Massey%2C%20based%20in%20the%20US%2C%20introduced%20us%20to%20Perveen%20Mistry%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20the%20first%20women%20Parsi%20lawyers%20in%20Bombay%20of%20the%201920s.%20This%20was%20a%20time%20when%20laws%20rampantly%20discriminated%20against%20women.%20Perveen%20launches%20her%20own%20struggle%20against%20these%20unjust%20laws.%20In%20an%20instance%20from%20Massey%E2%80%99s%20novel%20The%20Mistress%20of%20Bhatia%20House%2C%20Perveen%2C%20committed%20to%20the%20welfare%20of%20vulnerable%20domestic%20workers%20exploited%20by%20households%20they%20work%20for%20as%20well%20as%20by%20powerful%20men%2C%20intervenes%20in%20a%20discussion%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%20about%20the%20grant%20of%20bail%20to%20Sunanda%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BS%5Dhe%20had%20to%20remind%20the%20judge%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20Sunanda%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20homeless%2C%20nor%20was%20she%20unemployed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerveen%20squares%20her%20shoulders%2C%20lays%20her%20Swaine%20Adeney%20briefcase%20on%20the%20table%20and%20introduces%20herself%20to%20the%20magistrate%20as%20a%20solicitor%20employed%20at%20Mistry%20Law%2C%20number%20ten%20Bruce%20Street.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20counsel%20for%20Miss%20Chavda%2C%20a%20hardworking%20children%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Eayah%3C%2Fem%3E%20(nanny)%20in%20the%20household%20of%20Lord%20Dwarkanath%20Bhatia%20in%20Ghatkopar.%20I%20wish%20to%20explain%20why%20my%20client%20should%20not%20be%20required%20to%20pay%20bail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommanded%20by%20the%20judge%20to%20establish%20her%20credentials%2C%20Perveen%20tells%20him%20that%20she%20had%20completed%20the%20bachelor%20of%20civil%20law%20education%20at%20Oxford%20University.%20%E2%80%9CFollowing%20this%2C%20I%20clerked%20at%20Freshfields%20which%20granted%20me%20the%20rank%20of%20a%20solicitor.%E2%80%9D%20But%2C%20as%20the%20magistrate%20well%20knows%2C%20she%20could%20not%20take%20the%20law%20exam%20simply%20because%20women%20were%20not%20allowed%20to%20sit%20for%20the%20exam.%20Nor%20could%20she%20join%20the%20London%20or%20the%20Bombay%20Bar.%20An%20incensed%20magistrate%20tells%20her%20that%20she%20has%20no%20business%20to%20speak%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%2C%20and%20that%20she%20should%20be%20punished%20for%20this%20impertinence.%20He%20demands%20that%20she%20leaves%20the%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20intrepid%20lawyer%20has%20to%20tolerate%20the%20ridicule%20of%20her%20male%20colleagues%2C%20even%20as%20she%20comes%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20disappointing%20reality%20that%20she%20can%20never%20argue%20in%20a%20courtroom.%20She%20decides%20to%20continue%20her%20pursuit%20of%20justice%20by%20other%20means%2C%20such%20as%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20circumstances%20that%20led%20to%20Sunanda%E2%80%99s%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETowards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20novel%20Perveen%20requests%20the%20advocate%20general%20to%20release%20Sunanda.%20Her%20argument%20is%20a%20telling%20commentary%20on%20the%20vulnerability%20of%20women.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20an%20unmarried%20woman%20is%20exposed%20for%20having%20had%20intercourse%2C%20she%20is%20likely%20to%20lose%20the%20chance%20to%20work%20in%20a%20respectable%20occupation%2C%20or%20to%20remain%20accepted%20by%20her%20parents%20and%20family.%20She%20would%20likely%20never%20find%20a%20groom%20willing%20to%20take%20her%20in%20marriage.%20And%20she%20is%20only%20twenty%20years%20old.%E2%80%9D%20The%20argument%20is%20familiar.%20Even%20today%2C%20the%20law%20fails%20to%20protect%20women%20from%20their%20families%2C%20employers%2C%20and%20predatory%20males.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20from%20an%20earlier%20novel%20that%20Perveen%20Mistry%20has%20been%20in%20an%20abusive%20marriage.%20The%20law%2C%20however%2C%20does%20not%20sanction%20divorce%20on%20grounds%20of%20domestic%20violence.%20She%20now%20lives%20in%20her%20parental%20home%2C%20practices%20law%20in%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20firm%2C%20and%20passionately%20fights%20for%20justice%20for%20defenseless%20women.%20She%20is%20young%2C%20attractive%20and%20has%20enough%20confidence%20to%20enter%20into%20a%20relationship%20with%20a%20Britisher%2C%20Colin%2C%20even%20though%20she%20knows%20that%20the%20future%20of%20the%20affair%20is%20uncertain.%20Yet%20she%20is%20overcome%20with%20endearing%20uncertainty%20when%20she%20has%20to%20decide%20what%20to%20wear%20at%20the%20Lawyers%E2%80%99%20Ball.%20She%20%E2%80%9Cneeded%20to%20look%20just%20right%3B%20not%20so%20glamorous%20that%20others%20would%20doubt%20her%20ability%2C%20but%20she%20could%20not%20fade%20into%20the%20woodwork%E2%80%9D.%20Many%20professional%20women%20would%20understand%20her%20dilemma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20informal%20rules%20set%20by%20authors%20of%20classical%20detective%20fiction%2C%20from%20Conan%20Doyle%20to%20Agatha%20Christie%2C%20to%20Dorothy%20Sayers%2C%20in%20the%20early%20part%20of%20the%20twentieth%20century%2C%20the%20detective%20reconstructs%20the%20social%20context%20of%20a%20murder%20to%20negotiate%20the%20prime%20question%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98who%20done%20it%3F%E2%80%99%20No%20crime%2C%20let%20alone%20a%20murder%2C%20takes%20place%20in%20isolation%3B%20it%20is%20located%20in%20a%20social%20order%20that%20breeds%20greed%2C%20malice%2C%20desire%2C%20and%20violence.%20As%20our%20detective%20proceeds%20to%20uncover%20the%20dynamics%20behind%20a%20crime%2C%20she%20unearths%20the%20lies%2C%20the%20hypocrisy%20and%20the%20ugliness%20of%20society.%20This%20is%20the%20precise%20route%20followed%20by%20Perveen.%20Belonging%20to%20an%20upper-class%20and%20privileged%20Parsi%20household%2C%20she%20has%20access%20to%20other%20rich%20and%20powerful%20homes%20like%20that%20of%20Lord%20Dwarkanath%20Bhatia%20and%20his%20warring%20daughters-in-law%20who%20live%20in%20Ghatkopar%20ten%20miles%20from%20Bombay%2C%20and%20the%20mansion%20of%20a%20Nawab%20and%20his%20Australian%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerveen%E2%80%99s%20social%20status%20secures%20her%20access%20to%20the%20exclusionary%20Yacht%20Club%2C%20and%20the%20equally%20exclusive%20Taj%20hotel.%20She%20has%20the%20confidence%20to%20extract%20information%20from%20her%20British%20friends%2C%20and%20consult%20with%20Miriam%20Penkar%2C%20the%20sole%20Indian%20female%20obstetrician-gynecologist%20in%20Bombay.%20As%20the%20quintessential%20detective%20Perveen%20spots%20clues%20that%20are%20invisible%20to%20others%2C%20analyses%20the%20implications%20of%20random%20conversations%20with%20acuity%20and%20wisdom%2C%20and%20uses%20logical%20reasoning%20to%20construct%20an%20explanatory%20framework.%20She%20slowly%20and%20systematically%20uncovers%20a%20social%20order%20that%20preys%20on%20vulnerable%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20(late)%20P.D%20James%20wrote%20in%20her%20Talking%20About%20Detective%20Fiction%20that%20the%20detective%20novels%20must%20involve%20a%20mystery%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20book%20is%20solved%20satisfactorily%20and%20logically%2C%20not%20by%20good%20luck%20or%20intuition%2C%20but%20by%20intelligent%20deduction%20from%20clues%20that%20are%20honestly%2C%20if%20deceptively%2C%20presented.%20Murder%20remains%20a%20unique%20crime%2C%20and%20carries%20an%20atavistic%20weight%20of%20repugnance%2C%20fascination%20and%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMassey%E2%80%99s%20detective%20ably%20recreates%20the%20social%20context%20of%20Sunanda%E2%80%99s%20arrest.%20But%20the%20two%20murders%20that%20occur%20rather%20late%20in%20the%20book%20are%20not%20particularly%20interesting.%20They%20are%20not%20central%20to%20the%20story%20at%20all.%20The%20first%20murder%20appears%20as%20an%20afterthought%2C%20and%20the%20second%20as%20unnecessary%E2%80%93%20and%20both%20disappoint.%20We%20get%20the%20context%20but%20not%20enough%20of%20the%20text.%20The%20narrative%20could%20have%20proceeded%20without%20two%20people%20losing%20their%20lives%2C%20one%20by%20accident%20the%20other%20by%20design.%20The%20book%20can%20well%20be%20placed%20in%20the%20genre%20of%20feminist%20writing%20on%20the%20travails%20of%20women%20who%20confront%20unjust%20laws%20and%20brutal%20men.%20No%20one%20quite%20needed%20to%20be%20murdered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689923429000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21120717%2FUntitled-design-28.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fsolving-a-crime-in-old-bombay-and-also-exposing-discriminatory-laws-against-women%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sujata%20Massey%E2%80%99s%20latest%20whodunit%20brings%20back%20her%20intrepid%20Parsi%20lawyer%20Parveen%20Mistry.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fsolving-a-crime-in-old-bombay-and-also-exposing-discriminatory-laws-against-women%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taylor%20Sheridan%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Special%20Ops%3A%20Lioness%2C%E2%80%99%20Starring%20Nicole%20Kidman%20and%20Zoe%20Saldana%2C%20Is%20Shameless%20Military%20Propaganda%3A%20TV%20Review%22%2C%22content