20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20DW%E2%80%99s%20New%20Delhi%20bureau%20chief%2C%20Amrita%20Cheema%2C%20Habeck%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cyou%20can%E2%80%99t%20stay%20neutral%20if%20there%E2%80%99s%20injustice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20always%20an%20aggressor%20and%20one%20that%20is%20the%20victim%2C%20and%20if%20you%20say%20%E2%80%98I%20don%E2%80%99t%20distinguish%20between%20aggressor%20and%20victim%2C%E2%80%99%20in%20a%20way%2C%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20reflect%20the%20real%20situation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%20said%20while%20he%20respected%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20%E2%80%9Ctradition%20and%20partnership%20with%20Russia%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20country%20cannot%20remain%20neutral%20while%20the%20war%20is%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20would%20be%20very%20glad%2C%20and%20it%20would%20even%20help%20in%20our%20relationship%2C%20if%20India%20at%20least%20finds%20clear%20language%20and%20says%20this%20is%20an%20aggression%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20one-sided%20aggression%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20war%2C%E2%80%9D%20Habeck%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20officially%20maintained%20a%20neutral%20position%20since%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022.%20However%2C%20New%20Delhi%20has%20not%20supported%20Western%20sanctions%20on%20Moscow%2C%20and%20continues%20to%20purchase%20fossil%20fuels%20from%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgermany-china-india-diversify-robert-habeck%5C%22%3EGermany%20Cannot%20Decouple%20From%20China%2C%20But%20Like%20India%20Wants%20to%20Diversify%3A%20Vice%20Chancellor%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGermany%20looking%20to%20India%20as%20it%20%E2%80%98de-risks%E2%80%99%20from%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20friction%20over%20Ukraine%2C%20Habeck%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India%2C%20along%20with%20a%20business%20delegation%2C%20is%20a%20step%20toward%20expanding%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20economic%20ties%20in%20Asia%20away%20from%20China%20and%20to%20diversify%20energy%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCloser%20cooperation%20especially%20in%20renewable%20energies%20and%20green%20hydrogen%20holds%20a%20lot%20of%20potential%20for%20both%20sides%20and%20can%20increase%20our%20resilience%20and%20economic%20security%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20Economy%20Ministry%20statement%20released%20ahead%20of%20the%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%20told%20DW%20he%20was%20optimistic%20about%20collaboration%20with%20India%20on%20energy%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20face%20it%2C%20global%20warming%20is%20a%20reality%2C%20and%20we%20have%20to%20stop%20it%20as%20soon%20as%20we%20can%2C%E2%80%9D%20Habeck%2C%20who%20is%20a%20member%20of%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20Green%20Party%20said.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20renewable%20energy%2C%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20this%20is%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%20told%20DW%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20to%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20unprecedented%20aggression%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20we%20learned%20a%20painful%20lesson%20that%20being%20dependent%20on%20only%20one%20country%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20case%20on%20energy%20%E2%80%93%20can%20be%20dangerous.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20China%2C%20Habeck%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%E2%80%99s%20okay%20to%20have%20a%20big%20partnership%20with%20China%2C%20India%20also%20has%20one%2C%20but%20being%20dependent%20on%20one%20%5Bpartner%5D%20is%20not%20so%20good.%20So%2C%20we%20are%20searching%20for%20new%20partners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%20the%20German%20government%20published%20its%20first%20China%20strategy%20focusing%20on%20de-risking%20economically%20from%20China.%20Germany%20is%20China%E2%80%99s%20largest%20European%20trading%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELabor%2C%20free%20trade%20and%20energy%20on%20the%20agenda%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%2C%20who%20is%20joined%20by%20a%20business%20delegation%2C%20said%20he%20is%20also%20keen%20to%20address%C2%A0Germany%E2%80%99s%20shortage%20of%20skilled%20workers%2C%20which%20is%20a%20major%C2%A0concern%20for%C2%A0German%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20lack%20of%20workforce%20in%20Germany%2C%20in%20India%20%5Bthere%20are%5D%20a%20lot%20of%20skilled%2C%20talented%2C%20well-educated%20people%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20very%20welcome%2C%E2%80%9D%20Habeck%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGermany%20last%20month%20passed%C2%A0immigration%20law%20reform%C2%A0designed%20to%20encourage%20more%20people%20from%20outside%20the%20European%20Union%20to%20come%20to%20Germany%20for%20work.%20German%20Labor%20Minister%20Hubertus%20Heil%20is%20also%20visiting%20India%20this%20week%2C%20aiming%20to%20recruit%20more%20nurses%20amid%20a%20shortage%20of%C2%A0care%20workers%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHabeck%20also%20hoped%20for%20progress%20in%20the%20talks%20about%20a%20free%20trade%20deal%20between%20the%20EU%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EU%20and%20India%20have%20spent%20years%20attempting%20to%20hammer%20out%20a%20free%20trade%20agreement.%20During%20his%20February%20visit%20to%20India%2C%20German%20Chancellor%C2%A0Olaf%20Scholz%20expressed%20his%20desire%20to%20accelerate%20these%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20remainder%20of%20his%20trip%2C%20Habeck%20is%C2%A0scheduled%20to%20attend%20a%C2%A0Group%20of%2020%C2%A0energy%20ministers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20in%20western%20India%E2%80%99s%20Goa%20state%C2%A0on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3EDW%3Cem%3E.%20Read%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Findia-cant-stay-neutral-on-ukraine-war-germanys-habeck%2Fa-66301938%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689918171000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn